Certainly! Here's the code for the `Solution` class from the image:

```java
class Solution {
    public String toLowerCase(String str) {
        String result = "";
        for (char c : str.toCharArray()) {
            if (Character.isUpperCase(c)) {
                result = result + (char)(c + 32);
            } else {
                result = result + c;
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
}
```

This code converts a given string to lowercase by iterating through each character, checking if it is an uppercase letter, and converting it if necessary.
